# 1. PURPOSE

Defines runtime control for government core structures.

# 2. RUNTIME STATE

- active government-unit context
- governing-authority resolution state
- authority-term transition state
- legitimacy/stability publication state

# 3. EXECUTION RULES

- one active governing authority must resolve per authority scope and term window
- term transition must complete before authority publication
- legitimacy/stability state must be explicit before publication
- ambiguous governing authority is prohibited

# 4. FAILURE HANDLING

- missing government scope -> reject
- incompatible active term overlap -> reject
- ambiguous governing authority -> fail closed

